      "content": "yeah... that's exactly it. the silence. everytime i look at a new map or a new train schedule, i just feel this heavy weight. like i'm just dragging myself through scenery that doesn't mean anything anymore. it's exhausting to keep pretending there's another destination worth reaching. it feels like the most peaceful thing would be to just... close the guidebook for good. to just stop everything.",
